keyValuePair.Value: Can your team get beyond the Group Stage in this season's %1s?

This is where the serious stuff starts, the %1s Group Stage. You've looked at the teams you've been drawn against, and you will be aware of how your own team is developing. What are your thoughts? Are your boys good enough to fight their way through to the knock-out rounds this season?
It's all about consistency now.

I think we can be competitive, for sure. On our day, we can beat anyone. But the challenge for us is to be consistent and to avoid making the kind of mistakes which can prove so costly at this level. We have to be 100% ready for every game if we're going to progress.
We'll take it one game at a time.

I believe in my players. But I'm sure other managers will feel the same. It's important we make a good start and don't put pressure on ourselves by slipping behind in the table. We know what we have to do. Now we have to go out and prove we're good enough.

I'm very confident we've got a strong enough squad to compete at this level. I think the players believe in themselves and our intention will be to go out and try to win every game. I'll be disappointed if we aren't able to make progress this season.
Can your team reach the later stages of the %1s this season?

%1s presents your team with a different kind of challenge. And your supporters are hoping this can be your year, of course. How do you think your team is developing? Can you reach the later stages of the competition this season?
This is our first target.

For a club like ours, reaching the later stages is the absolute minimum requirement. The players are aware of what's expected of them and what we need to do to achieve our targets. Now it's about going into games with a positive and professional attitude.
We have to deal with the pressure.

The club's European ambitions put extra pressure on myself and the players, of course. But I'm confident we can handle our supporters' expectations. We have to stay calm now and approach these games in a professional way if we're going to make sure we reach the later stages.

Can your boys reach the %1s Final?
I'm sure you think your team has enough quality. Now it's about attitude and belief. Can your players handle the pressure that comes with trying to reach the %1s Final?
We know what we have to do.

I think reaching the Final is a minimum requirement for this club. We have our targets and our ambition is to compete at the very highest level. I think the players are good enough, yes. But now they have to go out and prove they are.
We have to handle expectations.

We're an ambitious club and reaching the Final has to be our target. That adds a bit of pressure ahead of every single game. My job is to make sure the players are properly prepared and strong enough mentally to cope with our supporters' expectations.
We're definitely good enough.

Can you win the %1s this season?
It'll be tough. There are plenty of good teams around. But you must be confident. Does your team have what it takes to actually go on and win the %1s this season?
We're ambitious.

Winning titles is what this club is all about. We have targets every season and they're always focused on lifting trophies not just competing for them. There are big expectation around the team but the boys will have to deal with that. We're going all out to win, like we always do.
We have to believe in ourselves.

We have a lot of quality in this squad but we'll be up against other good teams. Confidence will be very important. We need to be ready from the off. A couple of good wins will give the players self-belief and help us build up a little momentum.
This group of players can definitely win it.

We have a great group in our dressing room. I believe it's the best squad around. So that tells you what my ambitions are. Given the quality of the players and the stature of the club, I expect us to be going for the title each and every season.
